      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SOUTH SEAS ROCK NZ (2) has been down the track since kicking off in Australia with a win in this grade but has switched to Seaton Grima since last seen and was good in a recent trial when runner-up to topliner Don Hugo. Draws well and drops in class so could bounce back to winning form. DANCE WITH CARMER (1) worked when racing parked last start but had led from wider barriers to win two of his previous three outings so has the early speed to take advantage of the inside draw. GLITTER AINT GOLD (4) led and faded last time but had been very consistent with a string of placings prior. He deserves another chance. PERFECT STRIDE NZ (8) came from the outside barrier to miss by just a neck at this circuit and distance last start so respect.",
